                Multidisciplinary Care for Pancreatic Cancer
              </p>
              <div class="video-banner-layout3 bg-overlay mb-50">
                <img src="/assets/images/banners/19.jpg" alt="Pancreatic Cancer Treatment" loading="lazy" width="800" height="450">
                <a class="video__btn video__btn-white popup-video" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nrJtHemSPW4">
                  <div class="video__player">
                    <i class="fa fa-play"></i>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div><!-- /.video-banner -->
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Pancreatic cancer is a complex disease that requires a specialized, multidisciplinary approach. Our team at SALi includes surgical oncologists, medical oncologists, and gastroenterologists who are experts in treating pancreatic cancer.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Treatment options may include surgery (like the Whipple procedure), chemotherapy, and radiation therapy. We are committed to providing the most advanced and effective treatments while offering compassionate support to patients and their families.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Understanding Pancreatic Cancer</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Pancreatic adenocarcinoma is one of the most challenging cancers to treat, often diagnosed at advanced stages. Risk factors include smoking, chronic pancreatitis, diabetes, obesity, and family history. Early detection through imaging and biomarkers improves treatment outcomes.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Surgical Treatment Options</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Whipple Procedure (Pancreaticoduodenectomy):</strong> Complex surgery removing the head of the pancreas, duodenum, part of the stomach, and bile duct for cancers in the pancreatic head.</li>
                <li><strong>Distal Pancreatectomy:</strong> Removal of the tail and body of the pancreas, often with the spleen, for cancers in these regions.</li>
                <li><strong>Total Pancreatectomy:</strong> Complete removal of the pancreas in selected cases.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Chemotherapy and Radiation</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Chemotherapy regimens like FOLFIRINOX and gemcitabine-based combinations have shown improved survival in pancreatic cancer. Neoadjuvant therapy (before surgery) can downstage borderline resectable tumors, while adjuvant therapy (after surgery) reduces recurrence risk. Radiation therapy may be used in combination with chemotherapy for locally advanced disease.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Advanced and Metastatic Disease</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                For patients with advanced or metastatic pancreatic cancer, we offer palliative chemotherapy, pain management through celiac plexus blocks, biliary stenting for jaundice, and nutritional support. Our palliative care team works closely with oncologists to optimize quality of life.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Clinical Trials and Research</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                We participate in clinical trials investigating new treatment approaches for pancreatic cancer, including targeted therapy and immunotherapy. Eligible patients may have access to cutting-edge treatments not yet widely available.
              </p>
